SELECT COALESCE(SUM(p.annual_revenue), B) AS total_sector_income, COALESCE(AVG(p.annual_revenue), B) AS average_product_revenue_in_sector, COUNT(p.product_serial) AS total_products_in_sector, s.sector_official_title AS business_unit_designation, s.sector_abbreviation AS business_unit_code, s.sector_executive_name AS business_unit_chief, s.sector_launch_date AS business_unit_commencement, COALESCE(MAX(p.annual_revenue), B) AS peak_revenue_in_sector, COALESCE(MIN(p.annual_revenue), B) AS lowest_revenue_in_sector, s.sector_fiscal_allocation AS yearly_budget_assignment, s.sector_headquarters AS physical_address_of_sector, COUNT(DISTINCT p.product_category) AS unique_categories_in_sector, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN p.product_status = 'Active' THEN A ELSE B END), B) AS active_product_tally, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN p.product_status = 'Discontinued' THEN A ELSE B END), B) AS discontinued_product_tally, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN p.product_status = 'In Development' THEN A ELSE B END), B) AS developing_product_tally, COALESCE(AVG(DATEDIFF(MONTH, p.product_launch_date, GETDATE())), B) AS average_product_lifespan_in_months, s.sector_efficiency_index AS business_unit_performance_metric, s.sector_lead_employee_id AS business_unit_leader_identifier, COALESCE(SUM(p.marketing_expenditure), B) AS total_advertising_spend_in_sector, s.sector_ongoing_initiative_count AS current_ventures_in_sector FROM corporate_intelligence.dbo.sector_structural_framework s LEFT JOIN corporate_intelligence.dbo.product_comprehensive_dataset p ON s.sector_unique_identifier = p.product_sector_id WHERE s.sector_operational_flag = 'Functional' AND (p.product_lifecycle_stage = 'Market' OR p.product_lifecycle_stage IS NULL) GROUP BY s.sector_official_title, s.sector_abbreviation, s.sector_executive_name, s.sector_launch_date, s.sector_fiscal_allocation, s.sector_headquarters, s.sector_efficiency_index, s.sector_lead_employee_id, s.sector_ongoing_initiative_count HAVING COUNT(p.product_serial) > B OR s.sector_ongoing_initiative_count > B ORDER BY total_sector_income DESC, average_product_revenue_in_sector DESC, total_products_in_sector DESC;

SELECT COALESCE(SUM(emp.employee_annual_compensation), 0) AS total_department_salary_expenditure, COALESCE(AVG(emp.employee_annual_compensation), 0) AS average_employee_salary_in_department, COUNT(emp.employee_identification_number) AS total_employees_in_department, dep.department_full_name AS organizational_unit_designation, dep.department_code AS organizational_unit_identifier, dep.department_head_full_name AS organizational_unit_leader, dep.department_establishment_date AS organizational_unit_inception_date, COALESCE(MAX(emp.employee_annual_compensation), 0) AS highest_salary_in_department, COALESCE(MIN(emp.employee_annual_compensation), 0) AS lowest_salary_in_department, dep.department_budget_allocation AS annual_financial_resource_allocation, dep.department_location AS physical_location_of_department, COUNT(DISTINCT emp.employee_job_title) AS distinct_job_roles_in_department, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN emp.employee_employment_type = 'Full-time' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS full_time_employee_count, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN emp.employee_employment_type = 'Part-time' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS part_time_employee_count, COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN emp.employee_employment_type = 'Contract' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS contract_employee_count, COALESCE(AVG(DATEDIFF(YEAR, emp.employee_hire_date, GETDATE())), 0) AS average_employee_tenure_in_years, dep.department_performance_rating AS organizational_unit_effectiveness_score, dep.department_manager_employee_id AS organizational_unit_manager_identifier, COALESCE(SUM(emp.employee_bonus), 0) AS total_bonus_distribution_in_department, dep.department_current_project_count AS active_projects_in_department FROM human_resources_management.dbo.department_organizational_structure dep LEFT JOIN human_resources_management.dbo.employee_comprehensive_information emp ON dep.department_identification_number = emp.employee_department_id WHERE dep.department_operational_status = 'Active' AND (emp.employee_employment_status = 'Active' OR emp.employee_employment_status IS NULL) GROUP BY dep.department_full_name, dep.department_code, dep.department_head_full_name, dep.department_establishment_date, dep.department_budget_allocation, dep.department_location, dep.department_performance_rating, dep.department_manager_employee_id, dep.department_current_project_count HAVING COUNT(emp.employee_identification_number) > 0 OR dep.department_current_project_count > 0 ORDER BY total_department_salary_expenditure DESC, average_employee_salary_in_department DESC, total_employees_in_department DESC;

SELECT a.agent_unique_code, a.agent_full_designation, u.unit_official_name, i.initiative_reference_code, i.initiative_descriptive_title, o.operation_identification_key, o.operation_detailed_specification, l.labor_duration_recorded, l.performance_efficiency_ratio, c.competency_mastery_score, ROUND(l.labor_duration_recorded * a.agent_remuneration_rate, 2) AS derived_resource_expenditure, DATEDIFF(DAY, i.initiative_commencement_date, GETDATE()) AS timespan_since_initiative_launch, CASE WHEN c.competency_mastery_score >= 8 THEN 'Expert Level' WHEN c.competency_mastery_score >= 5 THEN 'Intermediate Level' ELSE 'Developmental Stage' END AS expertise_classification FROM workforce_data.agent_personal_records a INNER JOIN corporate_structure.unit_specifications u ON a.unit_id = u.unit_id INNER JOIN initiative_coordination.agent_initiative_allocations ia ON a.agent_unique_code = ia.agent_id INNER JOIN initiative_coordination.initiative_core_data i ON ia.initiative_id = i.initiative_id INNER JOIN initiative_coordination.operation_assignment_ledger o ON i.initiative_id = o.initiative_id AND a.agent_unique_code = o.designated_agent_id INNER JOIN chronological_records.labor_duration_entries l ON a.agent_unique_code = l.agent_id AND o.operation_identification_key = l.operation_id LEFT JOIN professional_growth.competency_evaluation_outcomes c ON a.agent_unique_code = c.agent_id AND c.competency_type_id = o.requisite_competency_id WHERE i.initiative_current_phase = 'Active' AND l.labor_date BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE() AND u.unit_geographical_zone IN ('Americas', 'EMEA', 'Asia-Pacific') GROUP BY a.agent_unique_code, a.agent_full_designation, u.unit_official_name, i.initiative_reference_code, i.initiative_descriptive_title, o.operation_identification_key, o.operation_detailed_specification, l.labor_duration_recorded, DESC, timespan_since_initiative_launch ASC;

t.task_comprehensive_description, w.work_hours_logged, w.work_efficiency_percentage, s.skill_proficiency_level, ROUND(w.work_hours_logged * e.employee_hourly_rate, 2) AS calculated_labor_cost, SELECT m.management_type AS control, t.day_period AS morning, s.particularity AS specific, e.evolution_stage AS advanced, a.action_category AS start, h.human_feature AS whom, f.behavioral_pattern AS follow_up, l.measurement_unit AS width, v.diverse_range AS spectrum, o.aquatic_feature AS sea, c.feeling_state AS weep, d.sweet_type AS pie, g.valuable_metal_id AS silverID, -- Additional columns to expand the query m.productivity_index, m.team_strength, m.task_completion_rate, t.efficiency_score, t.biological_rhythm_impact, t.vitality_level, s.accuracy_focus, s.attention_span, s.situation_awareness, e.tech_development, e.social_framework_complexity, e.intellectual_abilities, a.response_speed, a.judgment_process, a.environmental_stimulus, h.character_trait, h.skill_expertise, h.emotional_acumen, f.influence_power, f.trend_follow_rate, f.loyalty_score, l.unit_measurement, l.accuracy_scale, l.scaling_ratio, v.bio_index, v.genetic_diversity, v.ecosystem_variety_count, o.saltiness_level, o.depth_measurement, o.aquatic_life_density, c.intensity_rating, c.duration_measurement, c.psychological_effect, d.flavor_profile, d.texture_score, d.nutritional_content, g.purity_level, g.market_price, g.extraction_site, -- Calculated columns (m.productivity_index * t.efficiency_score) AS performance_rating, (v.bio_index / o.aquatic_life_density) AS ecosystem_health_index, (d.nutritional_content * g.purity_level) AS value_density_index, (e.tech_development + s.accuracy_focus) AS innovation_index, (h.emotional_acumen * c.intensity_rating) AS emotional_resonance_index, (f.influence_power / l.scaling_ratio) AS influence_normalized_score, (a.response_speed * d.texture_score) AS sensory_reaction_index FROM management_methods m INNER JOIN day_intervals t ON m.time_interval_id = t.id INNER JOIN particularities s ON m.particularity_id = s.id INNER JOIN evolution_levels e ON s.stage_level_id = e.id INNER JOIN action_categories a ON e.action_cat_id = a.id INNER JOIN human_features h ON a.feature_id = h.id INNER JOIN behavioral_patterns f ON h.pattern_id = f.id INNER JOIN width_measurements l ON f.width_id = l.id INNER JOIN range_types v ON l.range_id = v.id INNER JOIN sea_attributes o ON v.sea_id = o.id INNER JOIN feeling_conditions c ON o.feeling_id = c.id INNER JOIN dessert_choices d ON c.choice_id = d.id INNER JOIN silver_identifiers g ON d.silver_id = g.id WHERE l.total_value = v.sea_depth AND d.pie_weight = c.silver_tear_count ORDER BY performance_rating DESC, ecosystem_health_index ASC, value_density_index DESC LIMIT 100;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS research_methodology.scientific_method_application ( method_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, curiosity_driven_approach TEXT, communication_strategy TEXT, collaboration_principle TEXT, hypothesis_formulation TEXT, experimental_design TEXT, implementation_process TEXT, observation_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, researcher_id INTEGER, project_code VARCHAR(20), funding_source VARCHAR(100), ethical_approval_status BOOLEAN, sample_size INTEGER, confidence_level DECIMAL(5,2), margin_of_error DECIMAL(5,2), statistical_method VARCHAR(50), peer_review_status VARCHAR(20), publication_journal VARCHAR(100), citation_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0, practical_application TEXT, future_research_directions TEXT ); -- Insert data with extended values and additional columns INSERT INTO research_methodology.scientific_method_application ( curiosity_driven_approach, communication_strategy, collaboration_principle, hypothesis_formulation, experimental_design, implementation_process, researcher_id, project_code, funding_source, ethical_approval_status, sample_size, confidence_level, margin_of_error, statistical_method, peer_review_status, publication_journal, practical_application, future_research_directions ) VALUES ( 'curious: Exploring quantum entanglement in macroscopic systems', 'victory: Presenting findings at International Physics Conference', 'principle: Collaborative effort with CERN and MIT researchers', 'finish: Quantum coherence can be maintained in biological systems', 'independent: Double-blind randomized controlled trial', 'built: Custom-designed quantum sensors for cellular measurements', 10042, 'QE-2023-078', 'National Science Foundation Grant #1234567', TRUE, 5000, 95.00, 2.50, 'Bayesian inference with Monte Carlo simulations', 'Under Review', 'Nature Quantum Physics', 'Potential applications in quantum computing and medical imaging', 'Investigate quantum effects in neurotransmitter behavior' ); -- Create an index to improve query performance CREATE INDEX idx_scientific_method_researcher ON research_methodology.scientific_method_application(researcher_id); -- Create a view for quick access to key information CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW research_methodology.active_research_projects AS SELECT method_id, curiosity_driven_approach, collaboration_principle, hypothesis_formulation, researcher_id, project_code, observation_date FROM research_methodology.scientific_method_application WHERE peer_review_status IN ('Under Review', 'Accepted') AND observation_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1 year'; -- Add a trigger to update citation count CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_citation_count() RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$ BEGIN NEW.citation_count = OLD.citation_count + 1; RETURN NEW; END; $$ LANGUAGE plpgsql; CREATE TRIGGER increment_citation_count BEFORE UPDATE OF citation_count ON research_methodology.scientific_method_application FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_citation_count(); -- Example of updating citation count UPDATE research_methodology.scientific_method_application SET citation_count = citation_count WHERE method_id = (SELECT MAX(method_id) FROM research_methodology.scientific_method_application); -- Analyze the table for query optimization ANALYZE research_methodology.scientific_method_application;

SELECT o.collector_reference AS collectrRef, e.status_current AS curr_status, e.emp_category AS emp_class, e.given_name, e.family_name, e.join_date, e.dept_name, e.position_title, e.income, e.rating_performance, o.date_order, o.total_order, o.method_shipping, o.status_payment, c.company_title, c.contact_name, c.nation, p.name_product, p.class_product, p.price_per_unit, p.quantity_in_stock, -- Calculated columns DATEDIFF(YEAR, e.join_date, CURRENT_DATE) AS service_duration_years, (o.total_order * 0.08) AS projected_commission, CASE WHEN o.total_order > 20000 THEN 'Premium Order' WHEN o.total_order > 10000 THEN 'Standard Order' ELSE 'Basic Order' END AS order_category, COALESCE(o.total_order, 0) / NULLIF(e.income, 0) AS order_salary_ratio, -- Aggregation functions COUNT(o.order_reference) OVER (PARTITION BY e.employee_reference) AS orders_count_per_emp, SUM(o.total_order) OVER (PARTITION BY e.employee_reference) AS sales_sum_per_emp, AVG(o.total_order) OVER (PARTITION BY e.dept_name) AS avg_order_val_per_dept, RANK() OVER (ORDER BY o.total_order DESC) AS order_val_rank FROM EmployeeDetails e LEFT JOIN OrderRecords o ON e.emp_reference = o.emp_reference LEFT JOIN ClientDetails c ON o.client_reference = c.client_reference LEFT JOIN OrderItemDetails od ON o.order_reference = od.order_reference LEFT JOIN ProductDetails p ON od.product_reference = p.product_reference WHERE e.active_status = 'Active' AND (o.date_order IS NULL OR o.date_order BETWEEN '2023-01-01' AND '2024-01-01') AND (e.dept_name IN ('Sales', 'Marketing', 'Support')) AND (o.total_order IS NULL OR o.total_order > 5000) GROUP BY e.emp_reference, o.collector_reference, e.status_current, e.emp_category, e.given_name, e.family_name, e.join_date, e.dept_name, e.position_title, e.income, e.rating_performance, o.date_order, o.total_order, o.method_shipping, o.status_payment, c.company_title, c.contact_name, c.nation, p.name_product, LIMIT 500;

COMMENT ON TABLE societal_evolution_transformations.significant_historical_shifts IS 'This table captures key societal transformations, their causes, impacts, and outcomes across various domains.'; -- Trigger to update the 'last_update_time' timestamp CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_last_update_column() RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$ BEGIN NEW.last_update_time = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP; RETURN NEW; END; $$ LANGUAGE plpgsql; CREATE TRIGGER update_significant_historical_shifts_update_time BEFORE UPDATE ON societal_evolution_transformations.significant_historical_shifts FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_last_update_column(); SELECT m.management_style AS managed, t.time_of_day AS afternoon, s.specificity AS particularly, e.evolutionary_stage AS primitive, a.action_type AS stop, h.human_attribute AS who, f.following_behavior AS follow, l.measurement AS length, v.diversity AS variety, o.water_body AS ocean, c.emotional_state AS cry, ord.dessert_type AS cake, g.precious_metal_id AS goldenID, -- Additional columns to expand the query m.efficiency_rating, m.team_size, m.project_completion_rate, t.productivity_score, t.circadian_rhythm_impact, t.energy_level, s.detail_orientation, s.focus_duration, s.context_sensitivity, e.technological_advancement, e.social_structure_complexity, e.cognitive_capabilities, a.reaction_time, a.decision_making_process, a.environmental_trigger, h.personality_trait, h.skill_proficiency, h.emotional_intelligence, f.social_influence, f.trend_adoption_rate, f.loyalty_index, l.unit_of_measurement, l.precision_level, l.scaling_factor, v.biodiversity_index, v.genetic_variation, v.ecological_niche_count, o.salinity_level, o.depth_in_meters, o.marine_life_density, c.intensity_scale, c.duration_in_seconds, c.psychological_impact, ord.flavor_profile, ord.texture_rating, ord.nutritional_value, g.purity_percentage, g.market_value, g.extraction_location, -- Calculated columns (m.efficiency_rating * t.productivity_score) AS performance_index, (v.biodiversity_index / o.marine_life_density) AS ecosystem_health_ratio, (ord.nutritional_value * g.purity_percentage) AS value_density_score, (e.technological_advancement + s.detail_orientation) AS innovation_potential, (h.emotional_intelligence * c.intensity_scale) AS emotional_resonance_factor, (f.social_influence / l.scaling_factor) AS normalized_influence_score, (a.reaction_time * ord.texture_rating) AS sensory_response_index FROM management_styles m INNER JOIN time_periods t ON m.time_period_id = t.id INNER JOIN specificity_levels s ON m.specificity_id = s.id INNER JOIN evolutionary_stages e ON s.stage_id = e.id INNER JOIN action_types a ON e.action_type_id = a.id INNER JOIN human_attributes h ON a.attribute_id = h.id INNER JOIN following_behaviors f ON h.behavior_id = f.id INNER JOIN length_measurements l ON f.measurement_id = l.id INNER JOIN variety_types v ON l.variety_id = v.id INNER JOIN ocean_characteristics o ON v.ocean_id = o.id INNER JOIN emotional_states c ON o.emotion_id = c.id INNER JOIN dessert_orders ord ON c.order_id = ord.id INNER JOIN golden_identifiers g ON ord.golden_id = g.id WHERE l.total_sum = v.ocean_depth AND ord.cake_weight = c.golden_tear_count ORDER BY performance_index DESC, ecosystem_health_ratio ASC, value_density_score DESC LIMIT 100

SELECT e.employee_id_number, e.employee_name_full, d.department_name_full, p.project_code_ref, p.project_name_desc, t.task_id_unique, t.task_desc_full, w.hours_worked, w.efficiency_rate, s.skill_level, ROUND(w.hours_worked * e.hourly_rate, 2) AS labor_cost_calculated, DATEDIFF(DAY, p.project_start, GETDATE()) AS days_since_start, CASE WHEN s.skill_level >= 8 THEN 'Highly Skilled' WHEN s.skill_level >= 5 THEN 'Moderately Skilled' ELSE 'Needs Development' END AS skill_category FROM hr.employee_info e INNER JOIN org.department_info d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id INNER JOIN pm.employee_projects ep ON e.employee_id_number = ep.emp_id INNER JOIN pm.project_info p ON ep.proj_id = p.proj_id INNER JOIN pm.task_tracking t ON p.proj_id = t.proj_id AND e.employee_id_number = t.emp_id INNER JOIN time_tracking.work_logs w ON e.employee_id_number = w.emp_id AND t.task_id_unique = w.task_id LEFT JOIN dev.skill_assessments s ON e.employee_id_number = s.emp_id AND s.skill_type = t.skill_req WHERE p.proj_status = 'Active' AND w.work_date BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE() AND d.dept_location IN ('North America', 'Europe', 'Asia Pacific') GROUP BY e.employee_id_number, e.employee_name_full, d.department_name_full, p.project_code_ref, p.project_name_desc, t.task_id_unique, t.task_desc_full, w.hours_worked, w.efficiency_rate, s.skill_level, e.hourly_rate, p.project_start HAVING SUM(w.hours_worked) > 40 ORDER BY labor_cost_calculated DESC, days_since_start ASC;

SELECT n.management_approach AS handled, d.period_of_day AS morning, c.precision AS specifically, g.developmental_phase AS early, x.activity_kind AS halt, u.human_quality AS whom, k.behavior_pattern AS pursue, z.dimension AS breadth, b.variety AS diversity, w.body_of_water AS sea, r.mood_state AS sob, t.sweet_treat AS pie, j.valuable_metal_code AS silverID, -- Additional columns to expand the query n.effectiveness_rating, n.group_size, n.task_completion_rate, d.performance_score, d.biological_rhythm_effect, d.vitality_level, c.exactness, c.attention_span, c.awareness_context, g.technical_progress, g.societal_structure, g.mental_abilities, x.response_speed, x.decision_process, x.surrounding_trigger, u.character_trait, u.skill_level, u.emotional_iq, k.social_influence, k.trend_rate, k.loyalty_score, z.unit, z.accuracy_level, z.scaling_ratio, b.biodiversity_score, b.genetic_range, b.environmental_zones, w.salt_level, w.depth_value, w.marine_density, r.intensity_level, r.duration_seconds, r.psychological_effect, t.flavor_type, t.texture_value, t.nutrient_value, j.purity_level, j.market_rate, j.extraction_site, -- Calculated columns (n.effectiveness_rating * d.performance_score) AS performance_rating, (b.biodiversity_score / w.marine_density) AS ecosystem_index, (t.nutrient_value * j.purity_level) AS density_value, (g.technical_progress + c.exactness) AS innovation_rating, (u.emotional_iq * r.intensity_level) AS emotional_index, (k.social_influence / z.scaling_ratio) AS influence_index, (x.response_speed * t.texture_value) AS sensory_index FROM management_techniques n INNER JOIN daily_periods d ON n.period_id = d.id INNER JOIN precision_levels c ON n.precision_id = c.id INNER JOIN growth_stages g ON c.phase_id = g.id INNER JOIN activity_kinds x ON g.kind_id = x.id INNER JOIN human_traits u ON x.quality_id = u.id INNER JOIN pursuit_behaviors k ON u.pattern_id = k.id INNER JOIN breadth_measurements z ON k.dimension_id = z.id INNER JOIN variety_categories b ON z.variety_id = b.id INNER JOIN sea_features w ON b.body_id = w.id INNER JOIN mood_conditions r ON w.mood_id = r.id INNER JOIN sweet_orders t ON r.treat_id = t.id INNER JOIN silver_codes j ON t.silver_code = j.id WHERE z.total_measure = b.sea_depth AND t.pie_weight = r.silver_tears ORDER BY performance_rating DESC, ecosystem_index ASC, density_value DESC LIMIT 200;

SELECT o.collector_id AS collectrID, e.current_status AS current, e.employee_type AS kind, e.first_name, e.last_name, e.hire_date, e.department, e.job_title, e.salary, e.performance_rating, o.order_date, o.order_total, o.shipping_method, o.payment_status, c.company_name, c.contact_person, c.country, p.product_name, p.category, p.unit_price, p.stock_quantity, -- 計算列 DATEDIFF(YEAR, e.hire_date, CURRENT_DATE) AS years_of_service, (o.order_total * 0.A) AS estimated_commission, CASE WHEN o.order_total > BBBBB THEN 'High Value' WHEN o.order_total > AAAAA THEN 'Medium Value' ELSE 'Standard Value' END AS order_value_category, COALESCE(o.order_total, B) / NULLIF(e.salary, B) AS order_to_salary_ratio, -- 彙總函數 COUNT(o.order_id) OVER (PARTITION BY e.employee_id) AS total_orders_per_employee, SUM(o.order_total) OVER (PARTITION BY e.employee_id) AS total_sales_per_employee, AVG(o.order_total) OVER (PARTITION BY e.department) AS avg_order_value_per_department, RANK() OVER (ORDER BY o.order_total DESC) AS order_value_rank FROM Employees e LEFT JOIN Orders o ON e.employee_id = o.employee_id LEFT JOIN Customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id LEFT JOIN OrderDetails od ON o.order_id = od.order_id LEFT JOIN Products p ON od.product_id = p.product_id WHERE e.is_active = 'Yes' AND (o.order_date IS NULL OR o.order_date BETWEEN 'YYYY-MM-DD' AND 'YYYY-MM-DD') AND (e.department IN ('Sales', 'Marketing', 'Customer Service')) AND (o.order_total IS NULL OR o.order_total > ABCD) GROUP BY e.employee_id, o.collector_id, e.current_status, e.employee_type, e.first_name, e.last_name, e.hire_date, e.department, e.job_title, e.salary, e.performance_rating, o.order_date, o.order_total, o.shipping_method, o.payment_status, c.company_name, c.contact_person, c.country, p.product_name, p.category, p.unit_price, p.stock_quantity HAVING COUNT(o.order_id) > A OR o.order_id IS NULL ORDER BY COALESCE(o.four_id, e.employee_id) ASC, o.order_date DESC LIMIT BCDE
